Erika DeSouza tied a career high with 27 points and grabbed 15 rebounds, Lindsey Harding scored 25 points and the host Atlanta Dream (3-7) rallied for an 87-81 victory over the Liberty (4-5). Cappie Pondexter led the Liberty with 24 points.

¶ The former N.B.A. player Jose Ortiz was arrested in Puerto Rico after federal agents seized 218 marijuana plants at his house along with 40 rounds of assault-rifle ammunition, the United States attorney’s office said. Ortiz, 47, spent two seasons with the Utah Jazz, the last in 1990.